                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.113/10097: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-30T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. Following for your information.</p>
                <p>Department removed non-military aircraft destined to points in Mexico from
                    embargo on July 21 and requested Treasury Department to instruct the various
                    collectors of customs accordingly and to advise them that this ruling does not
                    apply to aircraft intended for hostile purposes or aircraft of a distinctly
                    military type.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
